The paper deals with constructing partitions of rectangles, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of a planar dual graph and restrictions on orientations of edges and junctions suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of listing all possible layouts in polynomial time suggests that the paper may also be relevant to graph theory (cs.GT) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
